lenders.name: Philip
lenders.occupational_info: Brighton and Hove Funeral Services One of the South East's leading funeral services, Brighton Funeral Services is located in Hove, just off Portland Road. We understand that arranging a funeral for a loved one will be one of the hardest things you've ever had to do. Brighton Funeral Services understands the hardship, which is why we handle all of the arrangements from the second you instruct us. The options available to you will give you the ability to plan a service unique to you and your family, as there are no rules on what a funeral service should include. Brighton Funeral Services offers a completely bespoke service from beginning to end to help you honour your loved one. Brighton Funeral Services For Care, Compassion, and Choice We can help you plan everything, from alternative to traditional funeral services, burial or cremation, and usually within your budget. We will assist you in making all the tough decisions, covering all of your options with you, and never making you feel rushed. Brighton Funeral Services will help you arrange the entire service and care of your loved one, and we can plan anything from a small personal gathering at your home, to a full traditional funeral service. Brighton Funeral Services values care, compassion, and choice above all else, and we go to great lengths to ensure we are responsive to your wishes during this trying time. Traditional and Alternative Services You will need to decide on the type of service you wish to have, in accordance with your loved one's last wishes. The traditional funeral option is generally a ceremony which tends to adhere to the ceremony of the more time honour ed funeral. These types of funerals often include a hearse, a minister to preside over the service and may include a local church. All the details of the ceremony will be influenced by whether or not religion plays a role, but the important point is that you have a choice. Today, many are looking to celebrate the life of the deceased rather than dwell upon the death, and as such alternative services are growing in popularity. Alternative services can include any number of elements, including woodland or eco-friendly burials, sea burials, cremation, and more. Secular and Celebrant Funeral Services in Brighton and Hove Celebrant services provide that important closing service to an individual's life while focusing on celebrating their life. These funeral services can be secular or religion, whichever you prefer. Philip, owner of Brighton Funeral Services, is a fully trained funeral celebrant that can aid you in planning a truly inspirational service that honours the memory of your loved one. Rest assured that all details will be covered in order to celebrate the life of your loved one. Caring Funeral Directors Available Twenty-four Hours a Day Brighton Funeral Service is here to assist you in this difficult time, so feel free to call us anytime, day or night, and we can even offer home visits if that suits you better. We staff a female funeral operative who can carry out all funeral preparation on the deceased. We will be there for you for everything from first contact through to the end. If you wish to discuss these matters we offer a free no obligation consultation. Call us any time, day or night, for care, compassion, and choice. Find out more about me. http://about.me/PhilipEvans11
